						               													<description>This revolutionary educational card game is winning hearts and minds by bringing out our inner wordsmiths! Last Say is a game that uses player creativity to create phrases from drawn cards. You'll have to get clever to make a great sentence. But be careful! Other players can steal your phrase and win the points!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Objective:&amp;#10;Get the ultimate Last Say by winning the most points!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Contents: &amp;#10;180 Cards&amp;#10;&amp;#10;How to Play:&amp;#10;Set up: &amp;#10;1. Each player draws 9 cards (3 of connecting words, and 2 each of nouns, verbs, and adjectives). Layout the cards on the table facing up (it does not matter if other players see your cards). After of your turn, replace used cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Play: &amp;#10;2. First player forms a sentence with their cards. When using a connecting word you can choose any of the 3 shown on the card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;3.Following players form a new phrase or steal by adding to a previous phrase. They may also replace their unwanted cards. &amp;#10;When it's the next turn of a player who's phrase was stolen, the last player who stole it collects the cards and wins the points. If nobody stole your phrase by your next turn, you win the points. It's a battle to get the &amp;#10;                             &amp;#10;                            LAST SAY!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;How to Win:&amp;#10;4. When one of the decks of cards is finished, count your points to see who won.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Points:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;+ 1 Point: Does not include all the colors.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;+2 Points: You steal by adding on to a phrase.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;+ 3 Points: Includes all the colors.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
